# .gitignore for GcashApp
# -------------------------------------------------------
# This file tells Git which files/folders to SKIP when saving your
# project to GitHub. You don't need to do anything with these files -
# Git just won't upload them.

# Compiled Java files - these get recreated automatically every time
# you run "javac", so there's no need to save them. Only the .java
# source files matter for grading.
bin/
*.class

# The database file - this gets created automatically the first time
# you run the program (with the two sample accounts). No need to
# upload it; anyone who runs the program gets a fresh one.
gcash.db

# Common IDE clutter (IntelliJ / Eclipse / VS Code project settings)
# - these are specific to your own computer and not needed by anyone
# else who opens the project.
.idea/
*.iml
.classpath
.project
.settings/
.vscode/

# OS clutter
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
